repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

body:
Add functions: `ascii`, `bin`, `format`, `hex`, `oct`
Add type: `range`

Looks like PyPy doesn't currently define `PyFilter_Type` and `PyZip_Type`, unlike CPython, but it defines `PyRange_Type`.

comment_data.body: This can go in `types_that_construct_their_instance` I think (although right now there isn't a huge advantage to doing that)

commit.message:
Update list of builtin functions and types.
Add functions: `format`, `hex`, `oct`.
Add type: `range`.
Fix test assertion, improve failure output.
Fix range transform after changing the type of 'range'.
Re-add 'xrange', now as type alias for 'range'.

milestone.description: First feature release after the cleanup releases 3.0 and 3.1.

title: Update list of builtin functions and types
